race.comment: JUMPING POWER TWO (4) was an impressive winner first-up over 1100m, stalking the pace before lengthening nicely to score by 2.7L lengths. The former Victorian can go right on with the job. DEBATING (3) raced a well-supported favourite in the same contest but faded late after setting the pace. Draws low again and keeps the top hoop. Comes back 100m and fitter he deserves another chance. BRYCE (1) resumes for the Cole yard and would be a chance if presented forward. May find this a touch short, but the 3kg claim brings him into it. STRAYA PRIDE (2) also resumes and has been competing in stronger. Usually needs one or two but respect the barn. Stablemate STARSPANGLEDANCER (5) would be around if she found her best.
